cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper is about creating and searching internal knowledge base articles for organizations using a real-time online learning-to-rank algorithm. The focus is on practical considerations for relevance scoring and algorithm deployment, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the use of conversational user feedback and natural language processing techniques for search quality improvement suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper's focus on user experience and handling events over the life-cycle of a KB deployment suggests that it may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories.
